# CPU Scheduling Comparison Project  
## Round Robin vs SRTF

---

## 📌 Project Description

This project implements and compares two CPU scheduling algorithms:

- Round Robin (RR)
- Shortest Remaining Time First (SRTF)

The system simulates process scheduling and compares both algorithms in terms of:
- Waiting Time (WT)
- Turnaround Time (TAT)
- Response Time (RT)
- Fairness and efficiency

It also visualizes execution using Gantt Charts.

---

## ⚙️ Requirements

- Programming Language: Java
- GUI Framework: Java Swing 
- Development Environment: Visual Studio Code
- 

---

 ## ▶️ How to Run

1. Open the project in Visual Studio Code or similar
2. Load all Java source files
3. Make sure JDK is configured
4. Run the main class (SchedulerGUI) using the IDE Run button
